Also significant has been the growing role of China in the Cuban economy, but China's influence will not be felt until the end of this period. Cuba would have to withstand the political backlash by President Obama of Cuba and China's increased aggressiveness in the region unless, of course, Colombia signs a free trade agreement with Cuba. This would help to quell the paranoid fear of many U.S. politicians that Cuba is secretly being flooded by Chinese goods.

Pablo Diaz (English/Puerto Rico)

It was the year of dealing with corruption scandals: there was the uncompromising rejection of the government by the population, and the oil spill of the Prestige allowed the left to recover from their previous years of attacks from the Spanish government.This year's news would be the dumping on Gripe A (Swine Flu) when it was first detected amongst residents in Puerto Rico. Adjustments in the number of cases confirmed were shown to be reduced depending on how the instance was defined, and health personnel have suffered numerous illnesses since they act in emergency response. The U.S. media speculated that the disease had mutations that could cause greater damage to human health, and by then the Spanish had largely enough precedent to understand what was at stake.
